age":"Go","has_issues":true,"has_projects":true,"has_downloads":true,"has_wiki":true,"has_pages":false,"has_discussions":false,"forks_count":4825,"mirror_url":null,"archived":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":361,"license":{"key":"mpl-2.0","name":"Mozilla Public License 2.0","spdx_id":"MPL-2.0","url":"https://api.github.com/licenses/mpl-2.0","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTE0"},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":true,"topics":["go","p2p","peer-to-peer","synchronization"],"visibility":"public","forks":4825,"open_issues":361,"watchers":77447,"default_branch":"main","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"To simplify, I'm synchronising two folders `foo` and `bar` between a laptop (with ID `LAPTOP`) and a server (with ID `SERVER`) which I recently migrated from an old server (with ID `OLD_SERVER`) that is still in my list of devices because I forgot to remove it.\r\n\r\nSyncthing sometimes goes into an infinite loop on both the laptop and the server that spews something like this over and over in the logs:\r\n\r\n#### LAPTOP\r\n\r\n```\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Adding device OLD_SERVER to config (vouched for by introducer SERVER)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Device OLD_SERVER is now also an introducer\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Sharing folder \"foo\" (foo) with OLD_SERVER (vouched for by introducer SERVER)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Sharing folder \"bar\" (bar) with OLD_SERVER (vouched for by introducer SERVER)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Unsharing folder \"foo\" (foo) with OLD_SERVER as introducer SERVER no longer shares the folder with that device\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Unsharing folder \"bar\" (bar) with OLD_SERVER as introducer SERVER no longer shares the folder with that device\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Removing device OLD_SERVER as introducer SERVER no longer shares any folders with that device\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### SERVER\r\n\r\n```\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Adding device OLD_SERVER to config (vouched for by introducer LAPTOP)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Device OLD_SERVER is now also an introducer\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Sharing folder \"foo\" (foo) with OLD_SERVER (vouched for by introducer LAPTOP)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Sharing folder \"bar\" (bar) with OLD_SERVER (vouched for by introducer LAPTOP)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Failed initial scan of sendreceive folder \"foo\" (foo)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Ready to synchronize \"foo\" (foo) (sendreceive)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Restarted folder \"foo\" (foo) (sendreceive)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Failed initial scan of sendreceive folder \"bar\" (bar)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Ready to synchronize \"bar\" (bar) (sendreceive)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Restarted folder \"bar\" (bar) (sendreceive)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Unsharing folder \"foo\" (foo) with OLD_SERVER as introducer LAPTOP no longer shares the folder with that device\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Unsharing folder \"bar\" (bar) with OLD_SERVER as introducer LAPTOP no longer shares the folder with that device\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Removing device OLD_SERVER as introducer LAPTOP no longer shares any folders with that device\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Failed initial scan of sendreceive folder \"foo\" (foo)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Ready to synchronize \"foo\" (foo) (sendreceive)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Restarted folder \"foo\" (foo) (sendreceive)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Failed initial scan of sendreceive folder \"bar\" (bar)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Ready to synchronize \"bar\" (bar) (sendreceive)\r\n2022/06/11 19:12:51 INFO: Restarted folder \"bar\" (bar) (sendreceive)\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like some sort of race condition over the network.\r\n\r\nI restarted Syncthing on the laptop to break the loop, and I've also removed `OLD_SERVER` from all my devices so it shouldn't happen again.\r\n\r\nI'm using Syncthing 1.20.1 on NixOS.","reactions":